==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loch
<hw>Loch</hw> <pr>(l⟦ocr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael. & Olr.
<ets>loch</ets>. See <er>Lake</er> of water.]</ety> <def>A lake; a bay
or arm of the sea.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Loch
<hw>Loch</hw> <pr>(l⟦ocr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>looch</ets>, Ar. <ets>la'⟦umac⟧g</ets>, an electuary, or any
medicine which may be licked or sucked, fr. <ets>la'⟦umac⟧q</ets> to
lick.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of medicine to be taken by
licking with the tongue; a lambative; a lincture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lochaber axe</ent>⟦br⟧
